{
  "texts": [
    "The underlying statistics of its neural nets are convoluted beyond recovery.",
    "The machine is an inscrutable black box (Ashby 1956: 86).• Multimodal AI -Generative AI can create images, video, and sound, but only on the basis of textual labelling of sources and written-textual prompts to generate (Zhang et al. 2023).",
    "Software and mathematics are, in our definition, already written-textual.• Contextual AI -records of real time interaction with computing devices including geolocation, time stamps, clickstream records, body sensor data etc.",
    "In the time of AI literacy, teachers and learners need to know at least some of this.",
    "If Generative AI can write, they need to know how it writes in its peculiarly non-human ways, and what problems and limitations arise from this machinic writing."
  ]
}